<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,788,887]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
Twenty-three species are recognized predominantly from Palaearctic Region, six Afrotropical species (two of them penetrate from the Palaearctic), and two Oriental species (
<bibRefCitation author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[804,1036,824,851]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref19407" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020 [&quot; 2018 &quot;]) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis box="[911,968,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Five species of this genus are distributed in Azerbaijan; one of them is newly recorded from Azerbaijan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
